Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #heavy-bottomed saucepan{}.
Cook @ground beef{1%lbs} in the heated oil, breaking the meat into tiny pieces, until brown.
Stir in @tomato paste{3/4%cup}, @peeled and chopped tomatoes{2.5%cups}, @grated
carrot{1}, @freshly ground pepper{1%tbsp}, and @basil{1%tbsp}.
-- you can substitute canned tomatoes
-- you can substitute 1 tbsp sugar for the carrot. 
Simmer for ~{30%minutes}.
-- add a little water if the sauce becomes too thick.
@salt{} to taste.
